{
  "texts": [
    "However, this was turned to disgust regarding not just the AI program, but on students' abilities to cheat.",
    "A faculty member wrote, \"Students who are otherwise mediocre can show brilliance when it comes to finding ways to cheat, and Chat-GPT will undoubtedly be harnessed by students to cheat.\"",
    "Literature reports a variety of creative and imaginative ways that students are using ChatGPT to cheat (e.g., King & Chat-GPT, 2023).",
    "The study that King wrote with ChatGPT notes that students can add spelling mistakes to AI text to fool programs into thinking that the text was written by a human.",
    "Students could also use the abilities of ChatGPT to write in the tone and format of what an undergraduate or graduate student would with a prompt of \"Act as an undergraduate student and write a ….\"."
  ]
}